  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 200°C (400°F).",
    "Season the lamb with salt and pepper.",
    "Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat and sear the lamb on all sides.",
    "Transfer the lamb to a baking sheet and roast in the oven for 15 minutes.",
    "Meanwhile, toast the binchotan charcoal in a skillet over medium heat.",
    "Chop the parsley and mint leaves and mix with garlic, lemon zest, red pepper flakes, and a pinch of salt and pepper.",
    "Remove the lamb from the oven and let rest for 5 minutes before slicing.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together red wine vinegar and honey.",
    "Serve the lamb with the chopped herb mixture and drizzle with the vinegar-honey glaze.",
    "Garnish with additional parsley and mint leaves, if desired.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
